{{lang: JSON}}

# Packaging the TypeScript service

`@athrio/loom-service-typescript` is the first loadable language service. A project installs it to give its TypeScript product an editor program of its own, held apart from the frame's. The package builds to one ES module, `dist/index.js`, whose default export is the service — the artifact the dynamic loader imports at runtime.

## The manifest {../package.json}

The `exports` field names the package's surface. The default entry, `.`, is the built `dist/index.js` — the loadable artifact whose default export is the service the loader reads. The `./TypescriptService` and `./ProductProgram` subpaths expose the source: `TypescriptService` is the language service a host activates, and `ProductProgram` is the TypeScript program it runs the product on.

The build bundles `volar-service-typescript` and Volar's language layers into the package, so the store needs nothing beyond the one file. Three things stay peers, supplied by the host that loads the service: `effect`, the `@athrio/loom-lang-services` contract that keys the `TypescriptSdk` capability, and the TypeScript compiler the editor runs. The build's runtime bridge reads those from the host instead of bundling a second copy that the dependency injection would never meet.

=>

{
  "name": "@athrio/loom-service-typescript",
  "version": "0.0.1",
  "description": "The loadable TypeScript language service: the product's own editor program, held apart from the frame.",
  "license": "Apache-2.0 OR MIT",
  "type": "module",
  "main": "./dist/index.js",
  "exports": {
    ".": "./dist/index.js",
    "./TypescriptService": "./src/TypescriptService.ts",
    "./ProductProgram": "./src/ProductProgram.ts"
  },
  "scripts": {
    "build": "vite build",
    "watch": "vite build --watch"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "@athrio/loom-lang-services": "workspace:*",
    "effect": "3.21.2",
    "typescript": "^6.0.3"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@athrio/loom-lang-services": "workspace:*",
    "@volar/language-core": "^2.4.28",
    "@volar/language-service": "^2.4.28",
    "@volar/typescript": "^2.4.28",
    "effect": "3.21.2",
    "typescript": "^6.0.3",
    "volar-service-typescript": "^0.0.71",
    "vscode-uri": "^3.1.0"
  }
}

## The TypeScript config {../tsconfig.json}

The config extends the workspace base, which supplies the compiler options and Node's types, and typechecks `src`. It never ships.

=>

{
  "extends": "../../tsconfig.base.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "out",
    "rootDir": "src"
  },
  "include": ["src"]
}
